"```sql\nSELECT \n    (SELECT COUNT(*) \n     FROM schools \n     WHERE County = 'Orange' \n       AND DOC = 54 \n       AND StatusType = 'Merged')::float / \n    (SELECT COUNT(*) \n     FROM schools \n     WHERE County = 'Orange' \n       AND DOC = 52 \n       AND StatusType = 'Merged') AS ratio\n```\nThis SQL query calculates the ratio of merged Unified School District schools to merged Elementary School District schools in Orange County. It uses subqueries to count the number of merged schools for each district type and then divides these counts to get the ratio."